A civic group, the Socio-Economic Rights and Accountability Project, has vowed to sue the Nigerian Government over the deactivation of the means of identification of human rights activist, Omoyele Sowore. Sowore on Wednesday revealed the deactivation of his passport, voter card, national identity card, and driver’s licence and other means of identification by the Federal Government. Omoyele Sowore
